init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "Little pig, little pig, let me come in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was like, "Dude, you're not going to shoot me."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I am," said P92, "and I'm going to use depleted uranium, because it's the most toxic substance known to man

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I don't want to live in this world any more," said the wolf, "and I'm going to eat you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm not going to let you in," said P92, "so you might as well go away."

actions.text: "I'm not going to heaven either," said the wolf.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm going to haunt you forever," said P92.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm going to haunt your dreams, and your nightmares, and your waking hours, and your bathroom breaks."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're not going to haunt me," said the wolf.
